  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community Health and Advancement Initiative (CHAI) Phase III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community Health and Advancement Initiative (CHAI) India, a collaboration between Tazo Tea/Starbucks and Mercy Corps, has been working since January 2003 in Darjeeling and February 2007 in Assam. The goal is to improve the economic and health conditions for tea estate residents and neighboring villages. CHAI works to democratically identify and address common problems through a community mobilization process to improve the quality of life through health, economic development, and youth initiatives. For 2009-2011, the CHAI Assam goal remains &#x201C;to diversify and integrate economic opportunities on tea estates in the Dibrugarh/Tinsukia Districts of Assam&#x201D;. Since beginning activities in February 2007, CHAI Assam has gained respect and support from tea owners, tea management, and senior government officials in Dibrugarh and Tinsukia Districts, largely based on the achievement to date. CHAI Assam&#x2019;s approach to increasing economic opportunities in rural tea communities is two pronged: 1) Provide financial services to entrepreneurs to start micro and small enterprises; and 2) Prepare youth for the workforce through education and skills building programs.  CHAI Darjeeling will build upon its successes and relationships with all stakeholders to achieve its goal of healthy and socio-economically strengthened CHAI communities.</narrative>
  </description>
